THE PILOT INITIATED A FLIGHT IN WEATHER WITH LOW VISIBILITY, RAIN AND FOG. THE 
PILOT HAD REPORTEDLY CHECKED THE WEATHER BUT DECIDED TO FLY ANYWAY. 
ABOUT 30 MINUTES AFTER TAKEOFF WHILE THE PILOT WAS MANEUVERING AT LOW 
ALT, THE AIRCRAFEET CRASHED IN A RIVER. THE AIRCRAFEET SANK IN 65 FEET OF WATER AND WAS 
NOT RECOVERED. AT THE TIME OF THE ACCIDENT, THE WATER WAS REPORTED TO 
HAVE BEEN 'GLASSY SMOOTH.' 
